JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1080
EP  - 1086
VL  - 28
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper considers the problem of maximizing the expected value of multicommodity flows in a network in which the arcs experience probabilistic loss rates. Consideration of probabilistic losses are relevant, particularly, in communication and transportation networks. An arc-chain formulation of the problem and an efficient algorithm for computing an optimal solution are provided. The algorithm involves a modified column generation technique for identifying a constrained chain. Computational experience with the algorithm is included.
AB  - This paper considers the problem of maximizing the expected value of multicommodity flows in a network in which the arcs experience probabilistic loss rates. Consideration of probabilistic losses are relevant, particularly, in communication and transportation networks. An arc-chain formulation of the problem and an efficient algorithm for computing an optimal solution are provided. The algorithm involves a modified column generation technique for identifying a constrained chain. Computational experience with the algorithm is included.
